{"PROTACTIC":[{"def":"Giving a previous narrative or explanation, as of the plot or personages of a play; introductory.","pos":""}],"PROTAGON":[{"def":"A nitrogenous phosphorized principle found in brain tissue.","pos":""}],"PROTAGONIST":[{"def":"One who takes the leading part in a drama; hence, one who takes lead in some great scene, enterprise, conflict, or the like.","pos":""}],"PROTAMIN":[{"def":"An amorphous nitrogenous substance found in the spermatic fluid of salmon.","pos":""}],"PROTANDRIC":[{"def":"Having male sexual organs while young, and female organs later in life.","pos":""}],"PROTASIS":[{"def":"The introductory or subordinate member of a sentence, generally of a conditional sentence; -- opposed to apodosis.","pos":""}],"PROTATIC":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to the protasis of an ancient play; introductory.","pos":""}]}